 Centane - Centane police are investigating the murder of a 50-year-old woman while her husband had gone to see his other wife. "It is alleged that the woman was left at home by her husband on Tuesday evening at Theko Fihla Locality, Tutura Village, Centane," described police spokesperson, Capt Jackson Manatha. "The husband went to his second home with his other wife as he had two wives." On Wednesday morning, at about 08:00, two young boys, who were sent to the homestead of the 50-year-old wife, found the door broken. "When the two boys entered, they saw the deceased with upper body injuries, already passed away. The boys called community members and the Centane Police were alerted." Capt Manatha said that no suspect(s) has been arrested for the murder yet. "Anyone who can assist Centane Police with the investigation to contact Centane Police at 047 498 1096/073 288 0340 or Crime Stop at 08600 10111." Eastern Cape SAPS Police Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Liziwe Ntshinga, has condemned the brutal murder of the defenceless woman. She vowed that Centane Police detectives will work around the clock to bring the suspect/s to book. "The identity of the deceased will be withheld until all her relatives are officially informed of her murder." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 